President Obama has declared a major disaster in the state of Wyoming due to flooding that occurred between June 4-18, 2010. This declaration allows for federal aid to supplement state and local recovery efforts in Fremont County and portions of the Wind River Indian Reservation. Federal funding will be available for emergency work, repair or replacement of damaged facilities, and hazard mitigation measures on a cost-sharing basis. Steven S. Ward has been named as the Federal Coordinating Officer for recovery operations in the affected area. Additional designations may be made in the future based on further damage assessments. For more information, contact FEMA at (202) 646-3272.